"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-12-03-olympic-prize-money-unfair-favours-elite-says-ioc\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"LAUSANNE, Switzerland (AFP) - Offering prize money at the Olympic Games was unfair and was shown at the Paris Games to favour a small number of elite athletes to the detriment to others, the International Olympic Committee (IOC) said Tuesday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.938088840271556, \"rank\": 0.06585594666536083, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 191, \"end\": 228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 191, \"end\": 228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"LAUSANNE\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 8}, {\"ngram\": \"(AFP\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 26}, {\"ngram\": \"Offering prize money\", \"from\": 30, \"to\": 50}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 71}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 100, \"to\": 115}, {\"ngram\": \"a small number\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 140}, {\"ngram\": \"elite athletes\", \"from\": 144, \"to\": 158}, {\"ngram\": \"the detriment\", \"from\": 162, \"to\": 175}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 185}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a taboo-busting move that sparked hugely mixed reactions, World Athletics president Sebastian Coe announced prize money of US$50,000 (47,000 euros) for every track and field winner at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 305, \"end\": 320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 3.053080030928052e-13, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 331, \"end\": 344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a taboo-busting move\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 267}, {\"ngram\": \"hugely mixed reactions\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 303}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 355, \"to\": 366}, {\"ngram\": \"47,000 euros\", \"from\": 381, \"to\": 393}, {\"ngram\": \"every track and field winner\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 427}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 449}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No other sports federation pays prize money at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 452, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No other sports federation\", \"from\": 452, \"to\": 478}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 484, \"to\": 495}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"IOC spokesman Mark Adams said that the IOC's executive board had discussed the topic of prize money distribution, raised by International Federations and athletes' representatives, on the first day of a meeting in Lausanne.\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 514, \"end\": 517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.252721009779172e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 528, \"end\": 538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"score\": 0.5137413298826524, \"rank\": 0.45833333333331644, \"text\": \"Mark Adams\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\"}, {\"begin\": 553, \"end\": 556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.252721009779172e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 638, \"end\": 663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_governing_body\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Federations\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_governing_body\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_governing_body\"}, {\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lausanne\", \"score\": 0.9999999984675014, \"rank\": 1.3967371059609892e-09, \"text\": \"Lausanne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lausanne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lausanne\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the topic\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money distribution\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 626}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes' representatives\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 693}, {\"ngram\": \"the first day\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 711}, {\"ngram\": \"a meeting\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 724}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There was a large amount of agreement on the topic, I might even say, unanimity,\\\" Adams said.\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 833, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a large amount\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"agreement\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 777}, {\"ngram\": \"the topic\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 790}, {\"ngram\": \"unanimity\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 819}, {\"ngram\": \"Adams\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 827}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was a question\\u2026 of principle, efficiency and distribution within the Olympic movement.\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 925, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a question\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 853}, {\"ngram\": \"principle\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 867}, {\"ngram\": \"efficiency\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"distribution\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 896}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic movement\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 924}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The biggest argument is one of fairness.\\\"\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 969, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The biggest argument\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"fairness\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 967}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adams' comments echo those made by IOC president Thomas Bach to AFP in April and come as seven candidates - including Coe - hone their campaigns to succeed the German as head of the Olympic body.\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 1166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1006, \"end\": 1009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.252721009779172e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1020, \"end\": 1031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 1035, \"end\": 1038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999975491551161, \"rank\": 2.0019353769389553e-06, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Adams' comments\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 986}, {\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1047}, {\"ngram\": \"seven candidates\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"Coe - hone\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1099}, {\"ngram\": \"their campaigns\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"head\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1145}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic body\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1165}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Paris Games, Adams said, \\\"if all the medallists, athletes and teams from all the sports were rewarded, it'd be about 1,000 athletes and teams who would benefit\\\".\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1336, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1186}, {\"ngram\": \"Adams\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1193}, {\"ngram\": \"all the medallists\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1222}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1232}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1242}, {\"ngram\": \"all the sports\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1262}, {\"ngram\": \"about 1,000 athletes\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1306}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1316}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They mostly come from what you might call the well-funded and privileged National Olympic Committees.\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1412, \"end\": 1439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9992949998050121, \"rank\": 0.0007054975709364635, \"text\": \"National Olympic Committees\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sixty five per cent of the individual medallists and teams winning medals are from 15 NOCs who were on top of the medal tally.\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1567, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sixty five per cent\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1460}, {\"ngram\": \"the individual medallists\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1499}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1514}, {\"ngram\": \"15 NOCs\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"top\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1547}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal tally\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1566}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It would only increase the existing inequalities even further\\u2026 it was felt by the executive board that this goes against the mission of the International Olympic Committee, and it could very easily downgrade the Olympic Games to an elitist event.\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1710, \"end\": 1741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the existing inequalities\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1618}, {\"ngram\": \"the executive board\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1667}, {\"ngram\": \"the mission\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1702}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1795}, {\"ngram\": \"an elitist event\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This was a principle supported by the participants, but particularly by the representatives of the IFs and as I said, by the athlete representatives, it's a matter of solidarity.\\\"\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 1998, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a principle\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"the participants\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 1869}, {\"ngram\": \"the representatives\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 1910}, {\"ngram\": \"the IFs\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1921}, {\"ngram\": \"the athlete representatives\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 1967}, {\"ngram\": \"a matter\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 1982}, {\"ngram\": \"solidarity\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 1996}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adams said that studies of the Paris Games showed that prize money \\\"would really overwhelmingly benefit a very, very small group of elite athletes to the detriment of others\\\".\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2175, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Adams\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"studies\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2023}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2042}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2066}, {\"ngram\": \"a very, very small group\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"elite athletes\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2146}, {\"ngram\": \"the detriment\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2163}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2173}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NOCs rather than international federations were free to motivate their athletes with prize money, he said, citing IOC president Bach's own experience with the German NOC after winning team foil fencing gold at the 1976 Montreal Games.\", \"from\": 2177, \"to\": 2411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2291, \"end\": 2294, \"title\": \"http://db